FBIS4-44110 "drweu123_h_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-123 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 GERMANY PDS Mayor Elected PDS Mayor Elected LD2706105794 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0952 GMT 27 Jun 94 LD2706105794 Berlin DDP/ADN German BFN [Excerpt] Kamenz (DDP/ADN) -- Hoyerswerda has become the first German town to elect a PDS [Party of Democratic Socialists] mayor. In the second round of voting in yesterday's local elections in Saxony, Horst-Dieter Braehmig gained 51.6 percent of the vote, clearly beating his SPD [Social Democratic Party] opponent and thus providing the most sensational result of the runoff elections. [passage omitted]
